source.name: State Energy Data System (SEDS)
source.description: EIA's State Energy Data System (SEDS) is a comprehensive data set that consists of annual time series estimates of State-level energy use by major economic sectors, energy production and and State-level energy price and expenditure data. Data are presented in physical units, BTUs, and dollars.
